This paper deals with secure beamforming in cognitive radio networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR). It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system engineering (cs.SY) aspects. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning (cs.MM) for classification purposes. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
